-- Dogan Agrees to Buy 2 Wind Power Plants for 240 Million Euros
-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 2012-05-29T12:23:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-29/dogan-agrees-to-buy-2-wind-power-plants-for-240-million-euros.html
Dogan Sirketler Grubu Holding AS (DOHOL) , a
Turkish group with interests in media and energy, agreed to buy
two wind-power plants from the Agaoglu group for 240 million
euros ($301 million).  Dogan will buy a 33-megawatts plant in southern Mersin
province and a 93-megawatts plant in western Balikesir province,
it said in a statement to the Istanbul Stock Exchange today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aydan Eksin in Istanbul at 
 aeksin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
